Iavan Pijoos, News24(Photo supplied IPSS Medical Rescue) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - Two people died and one person was left with minor injuries during a head on collision on the N2 Tugela Bridge on Sunday, IPSS Medical Rescue said. One female and one male, believed to be in their thirties, passed away after their light motor vehicle collided with a truck, IPSS spokesperson Dylan Meyrick said. Meyrick said they were both trapped in the vehicle. &nbsp; The truck rolled several times, but the driver escaped with minor injuries.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.